  "notes": "Primary source is the official RFEG club page (CAMPO DE GOLF ALTAONA, id=545), which lists the current 18-hole Altaona layout (re-established 2021 from the former Mosa Trajectum 27-hole complex; not double-counted). Internal consistency verified: pars sum to 72 (36/36), stroke indexes are a permutation of 1-18 (odd on front nine, even on back), and each tee's 18 per-hole meters sum exactly to RFEG's published totals (6217/5638/5077/4399). All four tees carry RFEG ratings for both genders. Cross-check: 18Birdies shows the identical par sequence and near-identical yellow-tee per-hole distances (older measurement, total 5770 m) but a different stroke-index allocation (e.g. SI 1 on hole 2 vs RFEG SI 1 on hole 9) — RFEG's current allocation is used. Golfshake lists slightly different yardage totals (Yellow 6236 yd, Red 4885 yd) with older SSS/slope figures (70/124, 72/113), likely a pre-rerating card. Stroke index shown is the RFEG allocation, common to all tees on the card."
